action.action-desc: Ms. Tlaib (for herself, Mr. Thanedar, Mr. Bergman, Mr. Moolenaar, Ms. Scholten, Mr. Huizenga, Mr. Walberg, Mrs. Dingell, Ms. Slotkin, Mr. Kildee, Mrs. McClain, Mr. James, and Ms. Stevens) introduced the following bill
Referred to the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure

form.official-title: To designate the Federal building located at 985 Michigan Avenue in Detroit, Michigan, as the Rosa Parks Federal Building, and for other purposes.

subsection.text: The Federal building located at 985 Michigan Avenue in Detroit, Michigan, shall be known and designated as the Rosa Parks Federal Building.

Any reference in a law, map, regulation, document, paper, or other record of the United States to the Federal building referred to in subsection (a) shall be deemed to be a reference to the Rosa Parks Federal Building.

paragraph.text: Sections 1 and 2 of Public Law 109–101 (119 Stat. 2171) are repealed.
